Alembic migration directory for Medi Check Backend.

## Purpose

This directory contains database schema migrations used by both local development and production deployments.

## How migrations are run

- Local development: run `uv run alembic upgrade head`
- Cloud Run deployment: run migrations before releasing traffic
- CI/CD: make sure the deployment pipeline can access the same `DATABASE_URL` used by the app

## Production notes

- Use the Cloud SQL PostgreSQL instance as the migration target.
- Keep the database URL in Secret Manager or another secure secret store.
- Run migrations before deploying a new Cloud Run revision if the schema changed.
- Do not rely on Cloud Run startup to apply migrations automatically.

## Common commands

```powershell
uv run alembic current
uv run alembic history
uv run alembic upgrade head
uv run alembic downgrade -1
```
